The Czech Republicâ€™s  PX (PX)  stock index
dropped for a second day, sliding 0.2 percent to 945.8 at the
close in Prague.  The following were among the most active  equities  on the
Prague Stock Exchange today. Stock symbols follow company names.  AAA Auto Group NV (AAA CP) rose 2.2 percent to 17.94 koruna
after the Czech chain of used-car dealerships said that Chief
Executive Officer Anthony Denny bought 320,209 shares for 5.7
million koruna ($291,440) yesterday.  Fortuna Entertainment Group NV (FORTUNA)   increased for a
second day, rising 0.5 percent to 98 koruna. The stock earlier
jumped as much as 4.4 percent, after the Czech bookmaker said it
received permission from the Polish finance ministry to start
